      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with documented test suite covering turbulence and scalar transport; change-control log for all model modifications.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023R2 is under institutional version control. Unit test coverage for the power-law hemolysis scalar transport module is partial; 14 of 22 regression tests pass at the required fidelity level. Change log for the February 2026 revision documents mesh topology change but lacks corresponding SQA sign-off. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to the hemolysis transport equation; order-of-accuracy confirmed within 5% of theoretical rate.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification confirms second-order spatial accuracy for velocity and pressure. Hemolysis scalar transport exhibits 1.7th-order convergence versus theoretical 2nd order; deviation attributed to near-wall power-law source term. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% for hemolysis index QoI on at least three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "GCI computed via Richardson extrapolation on 3.2M, 9.6M, and 28.8M cell meshes. GCI ranges from 2.1% to 4.8% across the five operating points; one high-speed point (6000 rpm, 5 LPM) reaches 4.8%, marginally within tolerance. Temporal discretization error not independently quantified. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (fluid temperature, hematocrit, anticoagulant protocol, pump speed, flow rate) documented and traceable; uncertainty budgets provided.",
      "rationale": "FDA test rig conditions documented in the 2025 Q4 dataset. Temperature controlled to 37 ± 0.5 °C; hematocrit 33 ± 2%. Anticoagulant lot traceability not recorded for two of five test runs. Uncertainty budget for flow rate measurement (Coriolis meter) provided; torque measurement uncertainty not propagated. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative metric (e.g., E_rms, validation uncertainty U_val) computed for hemolysis index across all operating points; metric evaluated against acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "Validation comparison performed against the 2025 Q4 experimental dataset. Normalised RMS error in hemolysis index is 18% across five operating points; acceptance threshold is 15%. Comparison was conducted against the pre-revision model; post-revision output comparison is planned but not available. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (normalised index of hemolysis, NIH; modified index of hemolysis, MIH) directly map to clinical hemolysis acceptance criteria; sensitivity analysis confirms QoI dominance.",
      "rationale": "NIH and MIH are the primary regulatory QoIs for VAD hemolysis. Sensitivity analysis via Morris screening confirms hemolysis scalar exponent (α) accounts for 61% of output variance. Plasma-free haemoglobin as a secondary QoI is modelled but not independently validated. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed on geometry, operating conditions, and fluid properties representative of the VAD COU; gaps between validation domain and COU domain quantified.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic pump geometry, not the proprietary VAD impeller. Operating speed range (3000–6000 rpm) partially overlaps VAD COU range (4500–8000 rpm). Gap analysis acknowledges extrapolation beyond validated speed range but does not quantify associated prediction uncertainty increment. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
