      "rationale": "No formal user qualification record exists for the analyst who executed the February 2026 revised model runs. Simulation setup checklist was applied for the 2025 Q4 runs but not re-executed post-revision. Independent peer review of boundary condition assignments not documented. Achieved level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by physics-based criteria; hemolysis damage model form validated against independent datasets; model form uncertainty quantified.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on prior rotating machinery literature. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger coefficients) used; alternative Lagrangian damage accumulation model considered but not implemented. Model form uncertainty estimated at ±35% on NIH via literature coefficient ranges; this exceeds the ±20% target for MRL 5. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters characterised with probability distributions; Monte Carlo UQ propagated through hemolysis predictions; P95 prediction interval reported.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed with 500 samples over six input parameters (viscosity coefficients, hemolysis exponents, inlet velocity profile). P95 prediction interval on NIH is +52%/-31% relative to nominal, exceeding the ±25% acceptance band. Input characterisation for blood temperature dependence of viscosity relies on the 2025 Q4 rheology data, which predates the model revision; updated rheology dataset (February 2026) was incorporated for viscosity but hemolysis coefficient distributions were not refreshed. Achieved level 2.",
      "note": "Primary experimental dataset (https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-experimental-2025q4) carries dataVintage 2025-10-01T00:00:00Z, which predates modelRevisionDate 2026-02-14T00:00:00Z. Re-validation is planned for Q2 2026."
    },
